24.title: A Clockwork Orange: Part 1
24.plot: In Part 1 of his four-part analysis of Stanley Kubrick's most controversial film, Leon discusses the Biblical undertones, neglect and possible sexual abuse that attributes to Alex's behavior.

25.title: A Clockwork Orange: Part 2
25.plot: In Part 2, Leon discusses the corrupt, totalitarian government regime and its methods of dealing with criminals and how that could also have an impact on Alex's behavior.

26.title: A Clockwork Orange: Part 3
26.plot: In continuing his analysis of Alex DeLarge's behavior, Leon examines a number of different factors: was he a bad egg from the start, simply a product of his time, or a negative side-effect of human experimentation?

27.title: A Clockwork Orange: Part 4
27.plot: In the conclusion of his Clockwork Orange analysis, Leon takes a look at sexual innuendo, the theme of dominance, and various instances of symbolism in both character and item placement, and discovers the true meaning of the film.
